# Portfolio Project Conventions

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router · React 19 · Tailwind v4 · TypeScript · shadcn/ui · Vercel
- AI: Vercel AI SDK (`ai` + `@ai-sdk/react`) · Anthropic claude-3-5-haiku
- Analytics: `@vercel/analytics` + `@vercel/speed-insights` (already in `app/layout.tsx`)

## File & Folder Structure

```
app/               # Routes and layouts only — no business logic
  api/
    chat/          # Streaming AI chat endpoint
    search/        # Semantic search endpoint
  devlog/          # MDX-powered devlog pages
components/
  sections/        # Full-page sections (hero, about, skills, projects, contact)
  chat/            # AI chat widget (client components)
  ui/              # shadcn-generated primitives — do NOT hand-edit
lib/
  ai/              # System prompt builders, AI utilities
  embeddings/      # Embedding generation and vector search helpers
  utils.ts         # cn() and other shared utilities
content/           # All site copy as typed TypeScript objects
  index.ts         # Barrel re-export for all content modules
  devlog/          # MDX files for devlog entries (*.mdx)
scripts/           # One-off ops (seed:embeddings, etc.) — not imported at runtime
```

## Components

- Default to **Server Components** — no `"use client"` unless the component uses browser APIs, event handlers, or React hooks.
- One component per file. File name matches the component name in kebab-case: `hero-section.tsx` exports `HeroSection`.
- Place section-level components in `components/sections/`. Place reusable UI in `components/`.
- AI/chat interactivity lives in `components/chat/` — all files there are `"use client"`.

## Content & Data

- All site copy (bio, projects, skills, certifications, etc.) lives in `content/` as typed TypeScript objects — never hardcoded in JSX.
- Export a single typed constant per file: `content/projects.ts` → `export const projects: Project[]`.
- Re-export everything through `content/index.ts` so imports stay clean: `import { projects, bio } from "@/content"`.
- **Adding a new project**: edit `content/projects.ts` only. The AI chat, semantic search, and project cards all derive from that single source. See the project skill for the full workflow.
- This content feeds the AI chat system prompt — keep it structured and machine-readable.

## TypeScript

- Prefer `type` over `interface` for object shapes.
- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow it, or define a proper type.
- Colocate types with the data they describe (e.g. `type Project` lives in `content/projects.ts`).

## Scripts

- `npm run dev` — local dev server
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm run seed:embeddings` — regenerate project embeddings (run after adding a project)
- Never import from `scripts/` in app code — scripts are standalone CLI tools.
